  "text": "Similar flows were observed in a numerical simulation by [CITATION_1] , albeit for a much lower Reynolds number, Re ≈ 1400-2000, where the free surface was assumed planar and modelled by a symmetry plane. In particular, their figures 2 and 3 share the main features of the rotationally symmetric flows described above. They may be described approximately as having a central region of synchronized rigid body rotation surrounded by an annular region of nearly irrotational flow. The resemblance is most pronounced in the shallow-water flow in their figure 2. In both cases, weak secondary flows are observed in the central region, but, as discussed above, their strength depends sensitively on the exact shape of the free surface.",
